In a statement released on Thursday afternoon, the Mandela family announced that the family s matriarch and former wife to late former president Nelson Mandela has been admitted to hospital, reports The Citizen.The cause of the 80-year-old s admission was not specified, but it is unexpected and she is being observed.She spent the night in Milpark Hospital in Johannesburg.They said: The Mandela family wish to inform the public that Winnie Madikizela-Mandela has been admitted to the Milpark Hospital for observation. Mrs Mandela went to the hospital for a routine medical check-up on Wednesday. A decision was taken to admit her for further observation. The family said they would announce any developments when they occur. Caxton News ServiceRead original story on citizen.co.za